===Noun===
'''brougham'''  (''plural:'' '''[[broughams]]''')

# a four-wheeled horse-drawn carriage, designed in 1839 by Lord Brougham. It had an open seat for the driver in front of the closed cabin for two or four passengers.
# an automobile, a sedan without a roof over driver's seat. 

